query_water_traction_bonus
Disk World creator help
query_water_traction_bonus

.SH Name
.SP 5 5
query_water_traction_bonus -  This function returns the bonus that objects get to move along the bottom or to resist such movement here.
.EP

.SH Syntax
.SI 5
int query_water_traction_bonus(object thing,
int buoyancy)
.EI

.SH Parameters
.SI 5
%^BOLD%^thing%^RESET%^ - the object that is moving along the bottom
%^BOLD%^buoyancy%^RESET%^ - the object's relative buoyancy
.EI

.SH Returns
.SI 5
the traction bonus on the bottom here.EI

.SH Defined in
.SI 5
/std/room/basic/water.c
.EI

.SH Description
.SP 5 5

This function returns the bonus that objects get to move along the bottom or
to resist such movement here.  If this should be anything unusual, such as
for a very smooth bottom or one with handles, this function should be masked
to return something different.
.EP

.SH See also
.SP 5 5
swim_exit, drift, calc_buoyancy

.EP

